The paper deals with the problem of preprocessing a convex polytope to efficiently determine whether a query point is inside or outside the polytope. This problem is related to computational geometry (cs.CG) and data structures (cs.DS). The paper also presents an application to nearest neighbor searching, which is a topic in numerical analysis (cs.NA) and machine learning (cs.LG). Finally, the paper involves the design and analysis of a data structure, which is a common theme in algorithms and data structures (cs.DM).
